Flongle Experiment 3 (F3) - 16-04-2021

Background

Two samples of two different haplotypes (FBM05 - used in F2, and LcDv70; 3 bp difference), one amplicon (Dv1F3, 725 bp), using the EXP-NBD104 Native Bacroding kit and LSK109 Ligation Sequencing kit.

  • MN24471
  • FA-03502
  • FLow-cell: AGG667 (pore QC: 30 available pores)

Run for 16 hours (starting: 27 pores).

Barcodes used:

  • BC01: CACAAAGACACCGACAACTTTCTT
  • BC02: ACAGACGACTACAAACGGAATCGA

Calculations for pooling barcodes:

For the ligation library prep: 70fmol in 30ul of pooled (barcoded) amplicon DNA is needed.

Using this equation I calculated the total ng needed for 70fmol

ugDNA = pmol DNA x 660pg/pmol x 1ug/10^6pg x 700bp

  • 1pmol = 1000fmol
  • 1ug = 1000ng

ugDNA = 0.07pmol x 660 x 1/10^6 x 700 = 0.03234ug = 30.234ng.

After barcoding each sample was nanodropped:

  • FBM05 = 11.1ng/ul in 15ul

  • LcDv70 = 9.8ng/ul in 15ul
    For approximately 30.2ng total - to be equimolar I added 15.1ng from each sample

  • FBM05 = 1.4ul

  • LcDv70 = 1.5ul

To make the final 30ul added 27.1ul water.

Demultiplexing and trimming adapters of pass reads using Porechop


porechop -i ./F3_HAC_pass_all.fastq --discard_middle -o ./Intermediate_files/F3_porechop_hacpass_all.fastq

  • --discard-middle removes any reads with an adapter found in the middle

  • default adapter threshold for porechop is 90% identity for both start and end adapters

  • default barcode threshold for porechop is 85% identity

  • 40,192 / 42,465 reads had adapters trimmed from their start (2,651,382 bp removed)

  • 34,679 / 42,465 reads had adapters trimmed from their end (1,716,735 bp removed)

  • 40 / 42,465 reads were discarded based on middle adapters

Trimmed reads then demultiplexed and saved to barcode-specific files:

Mapping to Sanger Sequence reference using minimap2 - Updated 2021-04-13

minimap2 -ax map-ont -t 12  ../../../F2_20200319/FBM05_Dv1F3.fas F3_trimmed_bc01.fastq --sam-hit-only > F3_trimmed_bc01.sam
minimap2 -ax map-ont -t 12  ../../../F2_20200319/FBM05_Dv1F3.fas F3_trimmed_bc02.fastq --sam-hit-only > F3_trimmed_bc02.sam
  • -ax map-ont generates CIGAR string and output alignments in the SAM format (-a) and uses the preset (-x) for ONT reads (-k 15 for minimizer k-mer length)
  • -t 12 12 threads (only used for mapping not indexing)
  • --sam-hit-only - output only mapped reads to SAM file

  • number of minimizers: 114 (99.18% singletons
  • number of reads mapped:
    1. BC01: 6213/6217
    2. BC02: 17698/17710

Full length sequences only - update 2021-04-21

Recap: Two samples (France FBM05, and Loch Creran LcDv70) barcoded (BC01 and BC02 respectively)

This time keeping only full length sequences (NanoFilt) mapped to: 1. The FBM05 Sanger reference 2. The LcDv70 Sanger reference 3. To both Sanger references

To keep only full length:

 NanoFilt BC01.fastq -q 9 -l 767 --maxlength 767 > F3_full_length_bc01.fastq
      #72
 NanoFilt BC02.fastq -q 9 -l 767 --maxlength 767 > F3_full_length_bc02.fastq
      #232

767bp is the length of the total amplicon including primer binding sites.

Trim primer binding sites:

  NanoFilt F3_full_length_bc01.fastq --headcrop 20 --tailcrop 22 > F3_full_length_trimmed_bc01.fastq
  NanoFilt F3_full_length_bc02.fastq --headcrop 20 --tailcrop 22 > F3_full_length_trimmed_bc02.fastq

Confusion matrix!

The number of sequences mapped to each reference was checked in Tablet.

BC01: - 56/72 mapped to FBM05 (correct) - 16/72 mapped to LcDv70 (wrong)

BC02: - 2/231 mapped to LcDv70 (wrong) - 229/231 mapped to FBM05 (correct)


library(caret)
lvs <- c("FBM05", "LcDv70")

truth <- factor(rep(lvs, times = c(72, 231)),
                levels = rev(lvs))
                
                
pred <- factor(
  c(
    rep(lvs, times = c(56, 16)),
    rep(lvs, times = c(2, 229))),
  levels = rev(lvs))


caret::confusionMatrix(pred, truth)

Accuracy is calculated as the number of correctly assigned reads(56 + 229) divided by the total (303)

Sensitivity is calculated as the proportion of BC02 reads were correctly assigned to LcDv70 (229/231), and specificity is calculated as the proportion of BC01 reads correctly assigned to FBM05 (56/72).

Figure 15. Confusion Matrix: Green cells = Correctly matched reads to reference, red cells = incorrectly matched.

Extra note on quality scores

I found a blog post that better illustrates the relationship between q-score and percent identity by wdecoster:

Figure A. Q-scores

Figure A. Percent Identity vs Average Base Quality Taken from blog post by wdecoster written 2018.

So a q-score of 9 is somewhere between 85-90% accuracy.
